<br>
Cook and John,<br>
     You asked if I had gotten that corpsman &quot;squared away&quot;...I'm still working on it.  He's truly a one-in-a-million man but the demons from that war have really created a lot of stumbling blocks.  I am in total awe of his courage in overcoming incredible obsticles, but the fear and rage of the &quot;dark side&quot; continue to haunt his life and hence mine.  It is sometimes so hard to reach someone who is alternately pushing you away and then claiming abandonment because he won't let me in, but not because I'm not trying!  <br><br>
For some reason, I keep thinking of when my first child was only a few weeks old and I was drying her off after her bath on the countertop.  Suddenly she started angrily screaming at the top of her lungs.  I madly started searching for a pin or something that could be injuring her.  When I looked up at her head I saw her little fist tightly gripping a tuft of hair on her head.  Of course the louder she screamed the tighter her grip.  I often think of that as a profound example of what we do in life. <br><br>
 I've learned a lot about getting past my own stubbornness and have stepped over my, up til now, very strong sense of pride almost every time to make the move to comfort him even when he has been the one attacking...It's really not a needy thing on my part, its just that I can't stand the thought of him being in pain alone.<br><br>
  But on the other hand, it sometimes feels manipulative and I go crazy vacillating between the two.  I have the patience of Job, but the frustration is sometimes overwhelming and his jealousy sometimes oppressive.  I'm loyal as a cocker spaniel and am not used to someone doubting my motives.  When he's more lucid he usually acknowledges that it isn't really about me as much as his own insecurities.  We've made a lot of progress in the 7 months we've been together - he says this is the deepest he's been able to go in a relationship since his divorce 20 years ago, but also says the deep feelings add to his vulnerability.  Two steps forward, one step back and then it suddenly feels like 40 steps back sometimes...I'm a pretty strong woman, but there are times when I feel like &quot;may day...I'm going down.&quot;<br><br>
Triage of the heart<br>
Too few fingers to cover every hole<br>
How do I stop the bleeding<br>
And not sacrifice my soul?<br><br>
Thanks for caring...<br><br>
ANNE
